@dguy @enothereska I have a few meta questions while reviewing this PR:

In the same class, in `onAssignment`,  `partitionToTaskIds` is computed as:

```
            Iterator<TaskId> iter = info.activeTasks.iterator();
            for (TopicPartition partition : partitions) {
            Set<TaskId> taskIds = partitionToTaskIds.get(partition);
            if (taskIds == null) {
                taskIds = new HashSet<>();
                partitionToTaskIds.put(partition, taskIds);
            }

            if (iter.hasNext()) {
                taskIds.add(iter.next());
            } else {
                TaskAssignmentException ex = new TaskAssignmentException(
                        "failed to find a task id for the partition=" + partition.toString() +
                        ", partitions=" + partitions.size() + ", assignmentInfo=" + info.toString()
                );
                log.error(ex.getMessage(), ex);
                throw ex;
            }
        }
```

which means that we assign each of the assigned partitions sequentially to each one of the active task, which seems not correct to me either. In addition, this field is only used in `StreamThread` for assigning partitions to the tasks to be created, which seems unnecessary.

Generally speaking, we need to know that when the thread is hosting multiple tasks and assigned with multiple partitions, which subset of partitions is assigned to each one of the hosting tasks. And in `AssignmentInfo`, the `standbyTasks` is a map from tasks to partitions, while the `activeTasks` is just a set of task ids. 

So could we make `activeTasks` as a map as well (with bumped version and handling older versions) and cleanup the logic to compute `partitionToTaskIds` since it is not needed anymore.

In addition, there are some redundant variables in `StreamPartitionAssignor` and `AssignmentInfo` such as `standbyTasks` and `partitionsByHostState`. Could we just let the assignor to keep the assignmentInfo as its internal variable which gets updated in `onAssignment`.

