something like

```
    KStreamBuilder builder = new KStreamBuilder();
    KStream<Key, Value> stream = builder.stream("mytopic");
    StateStoreSupplier stateStoreSupplier = new MyCustomSupplier("store-name");
    builder.addStateStore(stateStoreSupplier, false);
    stream.process(
        new ProcessorSupplier<Key, Value>() {
          @Override
          public Processor<Key, Value> get() {
            return new AbstractProcessor<Key, Value>() {
              private KeyValueStore<Key, Value> store;

              @Override
              public void init(ProcessorContext context) {
                super.init(context);
                store = (KeyValueStore<Key, Value>) context.getStateStore("store-name");
              }

              @Override
              public void process(Key key, Value value) {
                store.put(key, value);
              }
            };
          }
        }, "store-name"
    );
```

the use case for this is that i have a current changelog topic as input, and i want to inject a filter step before creating a ktable (in the above example that would happen right before the `process()`
